      "side": 1,
      "message": "`Login.vue` reads next from both `$route.query` and `window.location.search`. The router guard only uses `to.query.next`.\n\nFor bmcweb-style URLs like `/login?next\u003d/redfish/v1/Systems` (query outside the hash), an already-logged-in user gets sent to `/` instead of the Redfish URL. This is exactly scenario #3 in the commit message\u0027s manual test plan — it may fail depending on URL format.\n\nRecommendation: Extract a shared helper:\n```\nexport function getNextRedirectPath(route) {\n  const fromQuery \u003d route?.query?.next;\n  if (typeof fromQuery \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027string\u0027) return fromQuery;\n  return new URL(window.location.href).searchParams.get(\u0027next\u0027);\n}\n\n```\nUse it in both `Login.vue` and the router guard.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 24,
        "startChar": 57,
        "endLine": 24,
        "endChar": 71
      },
      "revId": "3fe27b75fc59939af05114e41f55c176470ee0d2",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
