      "writtenOn": "2026-05-27T04:30:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`isRedfishRedirectPath()` uses a string prefix check only. Paths with .. segments pass validation but normalize to non-Redfish destinations.\n`/redfish/v1/Systems/../../../../admin` resolves to `/admin`\n`/redfish/v1/../admin` resolves to `/redfish/admin`\n\nRecommendation: Validate the normalized pathname:\n```\nexport function isRedfishRedirectPath(path) {\n  if (typeof path !\u003d\u003d \u0027string\u0027 || !path.startsWith(\u0027/\u0027)) return false;\n  try {\n    const { pathname } \u003d new URL(path, \u0027https://example.com\u0027);\n    return pathname \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027/redfish/v1\u0027 || pathname.startsWith(\u0027/redfish/v1/\u0027);\n  } catch {\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n```",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 8,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 11,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "3fe27b75fc59939af05114e41f55c176470ee0d2",
